  "prompt": "Why am I getting Likes from people in India when my ad campaign is targeted only to people in SF?",
  "response": "If you're receiving likes from people in India while your ad campaign is targeted only to people in San Francisco, there could be a few reasons for this:\n\n1. **Ad Network Reach**: Some advertising platforms have broader reach capabilities. Even if you've targeted a specific location, your ad might still be shown to users outside your intended audience due to the platform's algorithms or audience overlaps.\n\n2. **Content Sharing**: If your ad content is shared by users in San Francisco, it may reach their friends or followers in other locations, including India. This could lead to likes from people who are not in your targeted area.\n\n3. **Interest-Based Targeting**: If your ad is targeted based on interests rather than strictly geographic location, individuals who share those interests might see your ad, even if they are located elsewhere.\n\n4. **VPN or Proxy Use**: Some users may use VPNs or proxies to appear as if they are in a different location. If users in India are using such tools, they could see and interact with your ad as if they were in San Francisco.\n\n5. **Ad Clicks and Engagement**: If users in India are clicking on your ad or engaging with it for any reason, they may inadvertently be liking it, regardless of your geographic targeting.\n\n6. **Misconfiguration or Errors**: Double-check your ad settings to ensure there are no misconfigurations. Sometimes, targeting options may not have been set correctly, leading to unintended audiences seeing your ads.\n\n7. **Audience Overlap**: If you have previously engaged with an audience that includes users from India, they might still be seeing your ads due to their prior interaction with your content.\n\nTo address this issue, you may want to refine your targeting options, monitor engagement metrics closely, and look for patterns in the likes you're receiving from unintended locations.",
